---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "May 15, 2026";
const effectiveDate = "May 15, 2026";

const sections = [
  { id: "scope", title: "1. Scope" },
  { id: "controller", title: "2. Data controller" },
  { id: "data-we-collect", title: "3. Data we collect" },
  { id: "purposes", title: "4. How we use data" },
  { id: "third-parties", title: "5. Third-party services" },
  { id: "ads", title: "6. Advertising & ATT" },
  { id: "subscriptions", title: "7. Subscriptions" },
  { id: "retention", title: "8. Retention" },
  { id: "transfers", title: "9. International transfers" },
  { id: "rights", title: "10. Your rights" },
  { id: "children", title: "11. Children" },
  { id: "changes", title: "12. Changes" },
  { id: "contact", title: "13. Contact" },
];
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Kârly collects, uses, and protects your data."
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
  effectiveDate={effectiveDate}
  sections={sections}
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Kârly</strong>, a mobile app
    published by <strong>NexUtility</strong> (referred to as
    <strong>"NexUtility"</strong>, <strong>"we"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>,
    or <strong>"our"</strong>), collects, uses, and protects information when
    you use the Kârly app or this website.
  </p>

  <p>
    We have written this policy in plain language and have included specific
    sections required by Apple App Tracking Transparency, Google Data Safety,
    the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and the KVKK.
  </p>

  <h2 id="scope">1. Scope</h2>
  <p>
    This policy covers the Kârly mobile app on Google Play (and, when
    available, on the Apple App Store) and the website at
    <code>karly.nexutility.dev</code>. It supplements the
    <a href="https://nexutility.dev/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">NexUtility umbrella privacy policy</a>;
    where the two disagree, this policy controls for the Kârly app.
  </p>

  <h2 id="controller">2. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    The data controller is NexUtility,
    <code>[Legal entity name]</code>, <code>[Registered address]</code>.
    Inquiries can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.dev">privacy@nexutility.dev</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="data-we-collect">3. Data we collect</h2>
  <p>
    Kârly is a calculator. The numbers you type (cost, sell price, currency,
    chosen marketplace, calculator results) are stored only on your device
    in the app's local storage. They are never sent to a NexUtility server.
    Uninstalling the app erases them.
  </p>

  <h3>3.1 Provided directly</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Calculator inputs</strong> — cost, sell price, marketplace
      selection, FX rate, optional operational costs. Stored on-device only.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact data</strong> — only if you write to
      <a href="mailto:support@nexutility.dev">support@nexutility.dev</a>: your
      email address and the contents of your message.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 Collected automatically</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Device & technical data</strong> — operating system version,
      device model, app version, language, anonymized crash diagnostics.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Anonymized usage events</strong> — feature opens, paywall views,
      and similar product events. Stored pseudonymously against an
      app-instance identifier and never linked to your calculator inputs or
      a real identity.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Advertising identifiers</strong> — on Android, the Advertising
      ID is used by Google AdMob to deliver ads. You can reset or opt out at
      any time in your device's system settings. On iOS, the IDFA is only
      accessed if you grant permission under App Tracking Transparency.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="purposes">4. How we use data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To run the calculator on your device.</li>
    <li>To verify subscription entitlement when you subscribe.</li>
    <li>To detect and fix crashes and bugs.</li>
    <li>To measure aggregate product usage and prioritize features.</li>
    <li>To serve ads in the free tier of the app.</li>
    <li>To comply with our legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="third-parties">5. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    Kârly relies on a small number of third-party processors. Each one has
    its own privacy policy, linked below.
  </p>

  <h3>5.1 Hosting & delivery</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosts this website and provides CDN /
      DDoS protection.
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.2 Subscription management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>RevenueCat</strong> — verifies Google Play (and App Store, when
      available) receipts and manages subscription entitlements. RevenueCat
      receives the store's anonymous identifier and a pseudonymous
      app-instance ID assigned by Kârly. It does not receive your calculator
      inputs.
      <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.3 Advertising</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google AdMob</strong> — serves ads in the free tier of Kârly.
      AdMob may use the Advertising ID (Android) / IDFA (iOS, with your
      permission), coarse location, and ad-interaction signals as described
      in the
      <a href="https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543" rel="noopener" target="_blank">AdMob Help Center</a>
      and Google's
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>.
      Personalized ads are only shown after we obtain consent where required
      by Apple's App Tracking Transparency or the IAB EU Transparency &
      Consent Framework.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.4 App stores</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google</strong> processes purchases under
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Apple</strong> (when iOS launches) will process purchases under
      <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="ads">6. Advertising & App Tracking Transparency</h2>
  <p>
    On Android, you can reset your Advertising ID or opt out of personalized
    ads at any time in system settings ("Privacy" → "Ads"). On iOS (when
    Kârly launches there), Kârly will request permission under App Tracking
    Transparency before any tracking that links your device to data collected
    by other companies. If you decline, you will still see ads — they will
    be non-personalized.
  </p>

  <h2 id="subscriptions">7. Subscriptions, restore & refunds</h2>
  <p>
    Kârly offers an optional subscription that removes ads and unlocks
    advanced features. Subscriptions are billed through Google Play (and,
    when iOS launches, Apple) at the price and period shown at purchase.
    Subscriptions auto-renew until cancelled at least 24 hours before the
    end of the current period.
  </p>
  <p>
    Refunds are handled by Google or Apple per their policies. We can help
    you find the right form on
    <a href="/support">/support</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="retention">8. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Calculator inputs stored on your device are retained until you clear app
    data or uninstall the app. Anonymized usage events and crash diagnostics
    are retained for up to 12 months. Subscription receipts are retained for
    as long as your subscription is active and for an additional period
    required by tax and accounting law, typically up to 10 years. Support
    tickets are kept for up to 24 months after the last reply.
  </p>

  <h2 id="transfers">9. International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our processors are located outside Türkiye and the European
    Union (for example in the United States). When personal data is
    transferred outside your country of residence, we rely on Standard
    Contractual Clauses or equivalent safeguards approved by the relevant
    data protection authority.
  </p>

  <h2 id="rights">10. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you have rights under GDPR, KVKK, and
    similar laws. These typically include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The right to access a copy of your personal data.</li>
    <li>The right to rectify inaccurate data.</li>
    <li>The right to erasure ("right to be forgotten").</li>
    <li>The right to restrict or object to processing.</li>
    <li>The right to data portability.</li>
    <li>The right to withdraw consent at any time.</li>
    <li>The right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.dev">privacy@nexutility.dev</a>. We
    will respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2 id="children">11. Children</h2>
  <p>
    Kârly is a business utility and is not directed to children under 13.
    We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe
    a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we
    will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="changes">12. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we
    will revise the "Last updated" date at the top. Material changes will
    be announced inside the app or on this page.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Privacy questions:
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.dev">privacy@nexutility.dev</a>
    <br />
    General support:
    <a href="mailto:support@nexutility.dev">support@nexutility.dev</a>
  </p>

  <p class="!mt-12 rounded-md border border-warning/30 bg-warning/5 p-4 text-sm text-fg-muted">
    <strong>Note for the team:</strong> Replace bracketed values (legal
    entity name, registered address) before submitting the app to Google
    Play and have this policy reviewed by counsel for the jurisdictions you
    ship to.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
